1. Create four users or more, each with their own home directory.

2. Form a minimum of two test groups.

3. Make numerous directories for solitary users.

4. Only a limited number of users will have access to the subject directory. All users can no longer access this directory.

5. Only a limited number of users will have access to the subject file. All users can no longer access this file.

6. A few users have access to root users' privileges. Other users are unable to access ROOT.

7. Other users have the ability to run certain instructions.

8. Every incident is recorded.
